'''Yasser Ibrahim Ahmed El Hanafi''' ({{langx|ar|يَاسِر إبرَاهِيْم أَحمَد الْحَنَفِي}}; born 10 February 1993) is an Egyptian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for [[Egyptian Premier League]] club [[Al Ahly SC|Al Ahly]] and the [[Egypt national football team|Egypt national team]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.youm7.com/News.asp?NewsID=1762870#.U8s3G_khjYA|title=ياسر إبراهيم جاهز لقيادة دفاع الزمالك أمام بتروجت - اليوم السابع|date=7 July 2014}}</ref>

== Club career ==

Born in [[Mansoura, Egypt]], Ibrahim began his football journey with the youth academy of his hometown club, Mansoura SC.

Ibrahim commenced his senior career at [[El Mansoura SC]], where he played from 2011 to 2013.

In 2013, he transferred to [[Zamalek SC]], making 10 league appearances and scoring once. During his tenure, he contributed to the team’s [[Egypt Cup]] victory in the 2013–14 season.

Initially joining [[Smouha SC]] on loan in 2014, Ibrahim’s move became permanent in 2015. Over four seasons, he amassed 80 league appearances and netted one goal.

On 7 January 2019, Ibrahim signed with [[Al Ahly SC]]. Since then, he has been instrumental in the club’s defense, contributing to multiple domestic and continental titles.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://alahlyegypt.com/2019/01/07/%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%B1-%D8%A5%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%87%D9%8A%D9%85-%D8%B6%D8%AD%D9%8A%D8%AA%D9%8F-%D9%85%D9%86-%D8%A3%D8%AC%D9%84-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D9%87%D9%84%D9%8A-%D9%88%D8%AF%D8%B9%D9%85/|title=ياسر إبراهيم: ضحيتُ من أجل الأهلي.. ودعم الجمهور طريقي إلى النجاح|publisher=alahlyegypt.com|date=7 January 2019|access-date=25 January 2019}}</ref>

== International career ==

On 2 December 2025, Ibrahim was called up to the Egypt squad for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/afcon2025/news/egypt-name-final-28-man-squad-for-totalenergies-caf-afcon-2025-salah-leads-pharaohs-charge/|title=Egypt name final 28-man squad for TotalEnergies CAF AFCON 2025, Salah leads Pharaohs' charge|publisher=[[Confederation of African Football]]|date=2 December 2025|access-date=12 December 2025}}</ref>

